  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Afghanistan: Reducing the Impact of Insecurity on Afghanistan&apos;s Legal System (RIIALS)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To support partner institutions, the Government of the
Islamic Republic of Afghanistan (GIROA), and international donors to gain a detailed understanding of the impact insecurity has on the development and capacity of the Afghan legal system and the available means to reduce that impact. 2) To enhance the organizational capacity of partner institutions to manage disruptive events and insecurity to be able to continue improving women&#x2019;s professional and meaningful participation in the justice sector, access to justice, and professional capacity.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries: Personnel of the partner institutions. Indirect beneficiaries: Afghan citizens seeking justice sector-related services.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to ameliorate the negative impact of insecurity on the continued development of the justice institutions of Afghanistan.</narrative>
  </description>
